<p>The Lakeside and Utica Road corridors contain Sterling Heights' largest homes, often exceeding 2,500 square feet, requiring 8-10kW solar systems and multi-zone HVAC solutions. These properties typically have the roof space and electrical infrastructure to support comprehensive energy efficiency upgrades. The Heritage Park and Clinton River areas feature a mix of ranch and colonial-style homes where solar panel placement requires careful consideration of roof angles and shading from mature trees. HOA regulations in newer subdivisions may impact solar panel placement and appearance, requiring consultation with architectural review committees before installation.</p>

